{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01WNobJ3HGaMiFRetRNJk6RB","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information needed. Let me compile a comprehensive report.\n\n## Cloche CLI Codebase Exploration Report\n\nI've thoroughly explored the `cmd/cloche/` directory and related files. Here's what I found:\n\n### 1. **CLI Framework Used**\nThe CLI uses **custom flag parsing** - no external CLI framework (not Cobra, not flag package). The main entry point manually parses `os.Args` and dispatches to appropriate command handlers. This is evident from the switch statement in `main.go` lines 31-47 and 66-88.\n\n### 2. **Commands Defined in cmd/cloche/**\n\nThe cloche CLI has **14 subcommands** split into two categories:\n\n#### Commands WITHOUT Daemon Connection (Lines 31-47):\n- `init` - Initialize a Cloche project\n- `health` - Show project health summary\n- `get` - Get a value from the run context store\n- `set` - Set a value in the run context store\n- `tasks` - Show task pipeline and assignment state\n\n#### Commands WITH Daemon Connection (Lines 66-88):\n- `run` - Launch a workflow run\n- `status` - Check run status\n- `logs` - Show logs for a run\n- `poll` - Wait for a run to finish\n- `list` - List runs for current project\n- `stop` - Stop a running workflow\n- `delete` - Delete a retained container\n- `loop` - Start/stop orchestration loop\n- `shutdown` - Shut down the daemon\n\n### 3. **Complete Subcommand Flags and Arguments**\n\n| Command | Required Args | Flags | File |\n|---------|---------------|-------|------|\n| `init` | None | `--workflow <name>` (default: \"develop\"), `--base-image <image>` (default: \"cloche-base:latest\") | init.go |\n| `health` | None | None | health.go |\n| `run` | `--workflow <name>` | `--prompt \"...\"` / `-p`, `--title \"...\"`, `--keep-container` | main.go |\n| `status` | `<run-id>` | None | main.go |\n| `logs` | `<run-id>` | `--step <name>`, `--type <full|script|llm>`, `--follow` / `-f` | main.go |\n| `poll` | `<run-id>` | None | poll.go |\n| `list` | None | `--all` (for all projects, default: current project) | main.go |\n| `stop` | `<run-id>` | None | main.go |\n| `delete` | `<container-or-run-id>` | None | main.go |\n| `tasks` | None | `--project <dir>` (default: current directory) | main.go |\n| `loop` | `[stop]` (optional subcommand) | `--max <n>` (default: use config) | main.go |\n| `get` | `<key>` | None | main.go |\n| `set` | `<key> <value\\|->` | None (supports `-` to read from stdin) | main.go |\n| `shutdown` | None | None | main.go |\n\n### 4. **Entry Point (main.go)**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go`\n\n- **Lines 24-29:** Check if command provided; if not, show usage and exit\n- **Lines 31-47:** Switch for commands that don't need daemon connection\n- **Lines 50-64:** Daemon connection setup using gRPC (Unix socket at `/tmp/cloche.sock` or custom `CLOCHE_ADDR` env var)\n- **Lines 66-88:** Switch for daemon-dependent commands\n- **Lines 91-114:** `usage()` function with complete command help text\n\n### 5. **Help/Usage Text**\n\nThe comprehensive usage text is defined in the `usage()` function (lines 91-114 of main.go):\n\n```\nusage: cloche <command> [args]\n\nCommands:\n  init [--workflow <name>] [--base-image <image>]\n                                             Initialize a Cloche project\n  health                                   Show project health summary\n  run --workflow <name> [--prompt \"...\"] [--title \"...\"] [--keep-container]\n                                             Launch a workflow run\n  status <run-id>                            Check run status\n  logs <run-id> [--step <name>] [--type <full|script|llm>] [--follow]\n                                             Show logs for a run\n  poll <run-id>                              Wait for a run to finish\n  list [--all]                                List runs for current project (--all for all projects)\n  stop <run-id>                              Stop a running workflow\n  delete <container-or-run-id>               Delete a retained container\n  tasks [--project <dir>]                     Show task pipeline and assignment state\n  loop [--max <n>]                            Start orchestration loop (default max=1)\n  loop stop                                  Stop orchestration loop\n  get <key>                                  Get a value from the run context store\n  set <key> <value|->                        Set a value in the run context store (- reads from stdin)\n  shutdown                                   Shut down the daemon\n```\n\n### 6. **File Organization**\n\n**Location:** `/workspace/cmd/cloche/`\n\n- `main.go` (15,097 bytes) - Main entry point with most command handlers (run, status, list, logs, stop, delete, loop, tasks, shutdown, get, set)\n- `init.go` (7,878 bytes) - Project initialization command with template generation\n- `health.go` (1,898 bytes) - Health summary command (HTTP-based)\n- `poll.go` (1,903 bytes) - Polling command for waiting on runs\n- `context_test.go` (3,046 bytes) - Tests for get/set context commands\n- `init_test.go` (7,103 bytes) - Tests for init command\n- `health_test.go` (477 bytes) - Tests for health command\n- `orchestrate_test.go` (446 bytes) - Tests for loop command\n\n### 7. **CLI Framework Details**\n\n- **No external framework** - Uses standard library `os.Args` for parsing\n- **Manual flag parsing** - Each command iterates through args and checks for known flags\n- **Positional argument support** - Some commands accept positional args (e.g., `cmdRun` accepts bare workflow name for backwards compatibility)\n- **stdin support** - `cmdSet` can read values from stdin when passed `-`\n- **Environment variables:** \n  - `CLOCHE_ADDR` - gRPC daemon address (default: `unix:///tmp/cloche.sock`)\n  - `CLOCHE_HTTP` - HTTP daemon address for health/tasks commands\n  - `CLOCHE_RUN_ID` - For get/set commands within a running workflow\n  - `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR` - For get/set context resolution\n\n### 8. **gRPC Service Dependencies**\n\nThe CLI uses gRPC (Google's RPC framework) to communicate with the daemon. Service definitions are in:\n\n**File:** `/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto`\n\nAvailable RPC methods:\n- `RunWorkflow` - Launch a workflow\n- `GetStatus` - Get run status\n- `StreamLogs` - Stream logs (with follow support via metadata)\n- `StopRun` - Stop a run\n- `ListRuns` - List runs\n- `Shutdown` - Shutdown daemon\n- `DeleteContainer` - Delete a container\n- `EnableLoop` - Enable orchestration loop\n- `DisableLoop` - Disable orchestration loop\n\nAll protobuf definitions generate Go code in `github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/api/clochepb`.\n\n### 9. **Key Implementation Details**\n\n- **Dependencies:** gRPC, protobuf, no CLI framework library\n- **Go Version:** 1.25.3\n- **Context handling:** Uses `context.WithTimeout()` for all gRPC calls (30-second default)\n- **Error handling:** Consistent pattern: print error to stderr, exit with code 1\n- **Backwards compatibility:** `cmdRun` accepts bare positional workflow name in addition to `--workflow` flag\n\n---\n\n## Summary Files\n- **Main CLI entry:** `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go`\n- **Command handlers:** All in `/workspace/cmd/cloche/` directory\n- **gRPC definitions:** `/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto`\n- **Dependencies:** `/workspace/go.mod` (uses gRPC, protobuf, toml, sqlite)"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: af5cd3fe4825115e9 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 36406\ntool_uses: 13\nduration_ms: 31834</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"43d3a283-4247-4cad-9b6c-2d2b3f0b0714","uuid":"2e4b4428-e5cd-4b8e-8eef-ab40adfdb37f","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the cloche CLI codebase thoroughly. I need to understand:\n1. How commands are currently defined in cmd/cloche/\n2. What subcommands exist and their flags/arguments\n3. How the CLI entry po