lth/tasks commands\n  - `CLOCHE_RUN_ID` - For get/set commands within a running workflow\n  - `CLOCHE_PROJECT_DIR` - For get/set context resolution\n\n### 8. **gRPC Service Dependencies**\n\nThe CLI uses gRPC (Google's RPC framework) to communicate with the daemon. Service definitions are in:\n\n**File:** `/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto`\n\nAvailable RPC methods:\n- `RunWorkflow` - Launch a workflow\n- `GetStatus` - Get run status\n- `StreamLogs` - Stream logs (with follow support via metadata)\n- `StopRun` - Stop a run\n- `ListRuns` - List runs\n- `Shutdown` - Shutdown daemon\n- `DeleteContainer` - Delete a container\n- `EnableLoop` - Enable orchestration loop\n- `DisableLoop` - Disable orchestration loop\n\nAll protobuf definitions generate Go code in `github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/api/clochepb`.\n\n### 9. **Key Implementation Details**\n\n- **Dependencies:** gRPC, protobuf, no CLI framework library\n- **Go Version:** 1.25.3\n- **Context handling:** Uses `context.WithTimeout()` for all gRPC calls (30-second default)\n- **Error handling:** Consistent pattern: print error to stderr, exit with code 1\n- **Backwards compatibility:** `cmdRun` accepts bare positional workflow name in addition to `--workflow` flag\n\n---\n\n## Summary Files\n- **Main CLI entry:** `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go`\n- **Command handlers:** All in `/workspace/cmd/cloche/` directory\n- **gRPC definitions:** `/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto`\n- **Dependencies:** `/workspace/go.mod` (uses gRPC, protobuf, toml, sqlite)"}],"totalDurationMs":31834,"totalTokens":36406,"totalToolUseCount":13,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1800,"cache_read_input_tokens":32508,"output_tokens":2097,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1800},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
